who killed the director.

55
00:03:03,101 --> 00:03:04,977
They contacted us to make
a deal in Los Angeles.

56
00:03:05,144 --> 00:03:08,064
<i>A deal? In exchange for
the notebook, right?</i>

57
00:03:08,981 --> 00:03:09,982
That's right.

58
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:11,818
I understand.

59
00:03:11,943 --> 00:03:14,153
I'll gather as many investigators as I can
in Los Angeles

60
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:15,863
without telling them the details...

61
00:03:15,947 --> 00:03:19,367
And use a satellite to
monitor the L.A. area.

62
00:03:20,535 --> 00:03:21,577
No...

63
00:03:22,453 --> 00:03:25,456
<i>I'll let you have
total authority on this, L.</i>

64
00:03:29,001 --> 00:03:30,002
Thank goodness.

65
00:03:30,545 --> 00:03:31,629
We make the decisions.

66
00:03:32,088 --> 00:03:35,758
But what was that about the Americans
not trusting L anymore?

67
00:03:37,969 --> 00:03:41,806
Near, are you sure about leaving
this to a fake L

68
00:03:41,889 --> 00:03:43,766
who hasn't succeeded
in catching Kira?

69
00:03:44,851 --> 00:03:46,602
So much the better.

70
00:03:47,687 --> 00:03:49,772
It means that there's a chance
we can take advantage of him.

71
00:03:50,273 --> 00:03:52,400
Of course, peoples' lives
are our first priority.

72
00:03:52,692 --> 00:03:56,028
But as the SPK, our goal is...simply...

73
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:59,615
to get the notebook and capture Kira.

74
00:04:01,951 --> 00:04:02,994
Light...

75
00:04:04,954 --> 00:04:10,793
I don't care if it costs me my life.
Please. . .just save Sayu...

76
00:04:12,795 --> 00:04:14,046
Don't say things like that!

77
00:04:15,131 --> 00:04:17,341
You may be satisfied with that...

78
00:04:17,508 --> 00:04:21,137
but do you know how painful it would be
for everyone you'd leave behind?!

79
00:04:22,263 --> 00:04:25,349
You cannot die in front of Sayu.

80
00:04:26,058 --> 00:04:28,603
You may lose contact with me.

81
00:04:29,353 --> 00:04:31,856
So if you ever come across
a situation where you have to

82
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:33,274
make a decision by yourself...

83
00:04:33,566 --> 00:04:37,069
do whatever you need to do to
make sure that both you and Sayu live.

84
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:39,447
Promise me that.

85
00:04:40,072 --> 00:04:41,157
Light...

86
00:04:43,451 --> 00:04:44,535
What? No way!

87
00:04:46,329 --> 00:04:48,289
I can really go with you?!

88
00:04:48,706 --> 00:04:53,044
Yeah. I may need your eyes
this time.

89
00:04:55,505 --> 00:04:56,756
All right!

90
00:04:56,964 --> 00:04:58,090
Thank you!

91
00:04:58,466 --> 00:05:00,635
I've got to start packing immediately!

92
00:05:10,895 --> 00:05:13,272
I can't decide...

93
00:05:13,564 --> 00:05:16,692
Hey, Light...
Which one do you like?

94
00:05:30,873 --> 00:05:34,544
If things get bad,
I'll have to kill Sayu...

95
00:05:44,846 --> 00:05:48,599
Dad, I'll go on ahead to Los Angeles
and make preparations.

96
00:05:49,642 --> 00:05:51,561
Mr. lde and the rest of you,
please come after us.

97
00:05:52,562 --> 00:05:56,649
We'll take different planes.
So just in case, Mr. Aizawa...

98
00:05:56,732 --> 00:05:59,694
will follow my father and ride
the same plane as him.

99
00:06:00,111 --> 00:06:01,112
All right.

100
00:06:01,487 --> 00:06:04,282
As a disguise,
I'll cut my hair.

101
00:06:06,617 --> 00:06:08,619
Okay everyone, I'm counting on you.

102
00:06:30,349 --> 00:06:31,559
Mr. Yagami.

103
00:06:31,726 --> 00:06:33,686
What is it?
Are you one of the kidnappers?

104
00:06:34,312 --> 00:06:38,441
You will take flight SE333.
I have your ticket.

105
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:40,776
Hurry. It's Gate 18.

106
00:06:41,527 --> 00:06:42,528
All right.

107
00:06:42,987 --> 00:06:45,281
A man has intercepted him at Narita!
Should I arrest him?

108
00:06:45,823 --> 00:06:47,950
Mr. Aizawa, calm down.

109
00:06:48,409 --> 00:06:51,871
It won't do us any good
if you arrest him right now.

110
00:06:52,371 --> 00:06:54,206
Just don't lose sight of him.

111
00:06:54,957 --> 00:06:56,459
Oh, no.

112
00:06:56,918 --> 00:06:58,961
The Deputy Director just got on
a different flight with that man

113
00:06:59,045 --> 00:07:00,254
than the one
he was supposed to catch...

114
00:07:00,421 --> 00:07:01,464
This is an emergency.

115
00:07:01,547 --> 00:07:03,716
- <i>I'm</i> going <i>to get on</i> as a <i>police officer...</i>
- <i>Calm down, Mr. A/zawa/</i>

116
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:06,969
If you do that and they find out
it will blow everything.

117
00:07:07,345 --> 00:07:08,471
Do you know where it's going?

118
00:07:09,055 --> 00:07:10,723
Umm... Oh...

119
00:07:11,265 --> 00:07:12,475
It's going to Los Angeles too.

120
00:07:13,392 --> 00:07:15,561
<i>Impossible, they even have a plane?</i>

121
00:07:15,728 --> 00:07:17,021
<i>This is bad...</i>

122
00:07:27,323 --> 00:07:31,661
<i>Flight SE333, Flight SE333,
can you hear me?!</i>

123
00:07:31,827 --> 00:07:33,412
<i>You are veering off course!</i>

124
00:07:34,413 --> 00:07:38,084
This is Flight SE333,
I hear you loud and clear.

125
00:07:38,793 --> 00:07:42,338
We are not off course.
I changed course.

126
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:43,965
<i>W-What are you talking about?</i>

127
00:07:44,382 --> 00:07:45,925
<i>What's wrong? Are you joking?</i>

128
00:07:46,926 --> 00:07:48,594
This is not a hijacking.

129
00:07:49,011 --> 00:07:52,723
We're just going to take a little detour
to drop off a passenger.

130
00:07:53,683 --> 00:07:55,768
<i>Feel free to track me by radar.</i>

131
00:07:55,935 --> 00:07:58,604
<i>But if you do anything
to interfere...</i>

132
00:07:59,063 --> 00:08:02,191
I will not hesitate to crash this plane
and take all the passengers with me.

133
00:08:07,655 --> 00:08:09,198
Light... I mean, L.

134
00:08:09,448 --> 00:08:10,741
The plane that
the Deputy Director is on

135
00:08:10,825 --> 00:08:12,201
has veered off course
from Los Angeles.

136
00:08:12,576 --> 00:08:14,620
Someone's going to be
dropped off somewhere...

137
00:08:14,787 --> 00:08:16,038
It's probably the Deputy Director...

138
00:08:16,622 --> 00:08:18,374
<i>Damn it! What's going on?!</i>

139
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:21,377
<i>I checked the flight crew
ahead of time.</i>

140
00:08:21,794 --> 00:08:23,421
<i>There wasn't anyone suspicious.</i>

141
00:08:24,672 --> 00:08:26,757
<i>The pilot is a veteran of
over fifteen years.</i>

142
00:08:26,966 --> 00:08:28,843
<i>There's no problem with
the co-pilot, either.</i>

143
00:08:29,468 --> 00:08:32,054
<i>So the enemy is powerful enough to
control ordinary people like them.</i>

144
00:08:34,306 --> 00:08:35,891
<i>Damn it. I've got no choice...</i>

145
00:08:39,895 --> 00:08:42,398
<i>Director, this is L. Get me N...</i>

146
00:08:42,982 --> 00:08:43,983
Yes.

147
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:47,236
<i>N, I think you know the situation.</i>

148
00:08:47,653 --> 00:08:52,783
<i>Can you notify the airlines, police
and military not to make a move yet?</i>

149
00:08:53,576 --> 00:08:56,328
What is L doing? How unreliable...

150
00:08:57,788 --> 00:08:59,415
All right...L.

151
00:08:59,707 --> 00:09:01,292
We'll figure out where he'll land...

152
00:09:01,459 --> 00:09:04,253
and keep surveillance over
the area by satellite.

153
00:09:05,421 --> 00:09:08,174
If there's anything else we can do,
please let me know.

154
00:09:11,635 --> 00:09:12,762
Take this PDA...

155
00:09:13,846 --> 00:09:15,389
Place the wireless earphone
in your ear.

156
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:24,648
<i>Yagami, only you can hear my voice.</i>

157
00:09:25,775 --> 00:09:26,776
<i>Listen closely.</i>

158
00:09:28,694 --> 00:09:31,447
I'm the one who kidnapped
your daughter.

159
00:09:32,990 --> 00:09:37,119
I have no interest in the lives
of you or your daughter.

160
00:09:37,912 --> 00:09:40,539
Right now,
the only thing I want is...

161
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:42,958
just the notebook.

162
00:09:44,919 --> 00:09:48,839
<i>If you do as I say,
I won't kill either of you.</i>

163
00:09:49,632 --> 00:09:51,592
<i>I've even arranged
an exchange procedure</i>

164
00:09:51,675 --> 00:09:53,886
<i>that you'll be satisfied with.</i>

165
00:09:54,929 --> 00:09:56,388
<i>Do not fight me.</i>

166
00:09:57,223 --> 00:10:00,017
<i>I am trading the killer notebook
for my daughter's life</i>

167
00:10:00,101 --> 00:10:02,228
<i>with an unknown person...</i>

168
00:10:03,479 --> 00:10:08,943
<i>When the time comes,
what do I do?</i>

169
00:10:10,611 --> 00:10:15,950
<i>As a police of fiber. ..
as a human being. . .as a parent...</i>

170
00:10:53,946 --> 00:10:55,906
L, we have pinpointed
where they have landed

171
00:10:55,990 --> 00:10:57,491
with our satellites.

172
00:10:58,075 --> 00:11:01,412
I'll send you footage
of what we're seeing.

173
00:11:02,121 --> 00:11:03,122
<i>Dad!</i>

174
00:11:04,832 --> 00:11:06,041
What's going on?

175
00:11:06,584 --> 00:11:08,502
How is he supposed to make
the exchange there?

176
00:11:27,188 --> 00:11:28,606
<i>You see it, don't you, Yagami?</i>

177
00:11:29,148 --> 00:11:30,191
<i>Enter there.</i>

178
00:11:30,691 --> 00:11:31,692
Underground, huh?

179
00:11:31,859 --> 00:11:33,527
This is interesting...

180
00:11:37,656 --> 00:11:39,617
<i>Damn it. Underground, huh?</i>

181
00:11:40,075 --> 00:11:42,369
<i>That means he predicted that
there 'd be satellite surveillance...</i>

182
00:11:43,037 --> 00:11:44,788
<i>Now I can't watch him...</i>

183
00:12:08,938 --> 00:12:11,523
It's bulletproof glass. You understand.

184
00:12:13,108 --> 00:12:16,362
A certain syndicate used this place
up until a few years ago...

185
00:12:16,445 --> 00:12:17,821
to make shady deals.

186
00:12:18,697 --> 00:12:20,199
We've made some modifications.

187
00:12:20,908 --> 00:12:22,660
Slide the notebook through here.

188
00:12:23,577 --> 00:12:26,538
When you slide it in,
I'll release this handle.

189
00:12:27,164 --> 00:12:30,376
We'll step back and
spin the glass door.

190
00:12:30,459 --> 00:12:32,211
The notebook will
be passed this way

191
00:12:32,294 --> 00:12:33,337
and your daughter, to you.

192
00:12:33,963 --> 00:12:37,049
If you don't go through with the trade,
I'll shoot your daughter from here...

193
00:12:45,015 --> 00:12:46,934
<i>L, do you have a plan?</i>

194
00:12:47,434 --> 00:12:49,019
Or do you really think it's all right

195
00:12:49,103 --> 00:12:53,190
to let the notebook fall into the
hands of someone you don't know?

196
00:12:54,441 --> 00:12:56,568
Y462, begin.

197
00:12:57,444 --> 00:12:59,238
Now open the notebook
and slide it into...

198
00:12:59,321 --> 00:13:02,074
the slot in the glass door
to the left.

199
00:13:08,539 --> 00:13:11,041
<i>Damn it.
I'm being set back even further...</i>

200
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:14,628
<i>I've just arrived in L.A.
and I'm not in any situation</i>

201
00:13:14,712 --> 00:13:17,548
<i>to be giving orders to the police
agencies around the world as L...</i>

202
00:13:18,465 --> 00:13:20,509
<i>At this rate. . .the notebook will...</i>

203
00:13:21,468 --> 00:13:22,636
Light, what's wrong?

204
00:13:23,178 --> 00:13:25,180
Are you all right? You're pale...

205
00:13:25,347 --> 00:13:27,224
Misa, shut up and just do as I say!

206
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:32,604
I want you to take more care than usual
in killing the criminals in Japan.

207
00:13:33,605 --> 00:13:35,649
He's investigating Kira.

208
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:37,860
You know something bad
will happen

209
00:13:37,943 --> 00:13:39,486
if the punishing gets delayed,
don't you?

210
00:13:40,195 --> 00:13:42,573
Okay... But who's "he"?

211
00:13:42,656 --> 00:13:43,991
Just do as I say!

212
00:13:45,117 --> 00:13:46,327
You're just taking out
your anger on her.

213
00:13:53,959 --> 00:13:55,127
<i>I-I can still make it...</i>

214
00:13:55,961 --> 00:13:59,506
<i>At this rate,
is my only option to kill Sayu?</i>

215
00:14:01,383 --> 00:14:03,427
All right, I'm going to
test the out notebook.

216
00:14:03,802 --> 00:14:05,929
"Test out?!"
Are you going to kill someone?!

217
00:14:06,263 --> 00:14:07,431
- That's...
- Hey, hey...

218
00:14:08,349 --> 00:14:10,559
We can't trade
without testing it out.

219
00:14:11,894 --> 00:14:13,645
Do you want
your daughter to die?

220
00:14:26,825 --> 00:14:27,910
<i>This is not good!</i>

221
00:14:28,369 --> 00:14:30,871
<i>Only the police
know about this case.</i>

222
00:14:31,372 --> 00:14:33,457
<i>I can't blame
Sayu's death on Kira...</i>

223
00:14:38,921 --> 00:14:40,506
What's wrong?!
Are you all right, Miller?!

224
00:14:41,632 --> 00:14:44,968
That's what you get when you steal and
sell our drugs behind my back.

225
00:14:45,719 --> 00:14:47,304
He was worthless,

226
00:14:47,388 --> 00:14:49,014
but this is the first time
he's been useful.

227
00:14:49,556 --> 00:14:52,226
Y462, the target is dead.

228
00:14:54,103 --> 00:14:56,063
It seems the notebook is real.

229
00:14:56,980 --> 00:15:00,109
Now let go.
We'll exchange it for your daughter.

230
00:15:08,992 --> 00:15:10,661
<i>Sayu. .. Dad...</i>

231
00:15:10,994 --> 00:15:12,663
Oh, they've been saved.

232
00:15:13,539 --> 00:15:15,207
The perpetrator is headed
for a helicopter.

233
00:15:15,624 --> 00:15:18,293
We can assume that
that's his means of escape.

234
00:15:19,378 --> 00:15:22,673
This means that the notebook
